    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-17T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-17T01:00:00-05:00" n="622"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.01/3805: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hamilton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-17T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 17, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1754. See Embassy’s 1666, May 12, 10 a.m. and previous.<note n="86"
                        xml:id="d622fn86">Not printed.</note> The following is a paraphrased
                    translation of a note from Molotov dated May 16.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“The Soviet Government, having studied the draft directive<note n="87"
                            xml:id="d622fn87">See telegram 836, April 8, 3 p.m., to Moscow, <ref
                                target="#pg_675">p. 675</ref>.</note> to General Eisenhower in the
                        event of the occupation of French territory contained in your letters of
                        April 11 and May 10, has reached the conclusion that the requirements of the
                        military situation which will <pb facs="0700" n="688" xml:id="pg_688"/> be
                        created as the result of an invasion of the territory of France by Allied
                        forces are met by this directive.</p>
                    <p>I shall be grateful if you will transmit the above to the United States
                        Government.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
